properties.name: Beach Camping at the Lost TV Show Set.
properties.description: Posted by Ianline   I camped out on the beach here for a few nights. One tip of advice when camping... Don\'t camp near a movie or TV show set... They keep really bright lights on at night. I camped out next to the plane crash set for the TV show Lost. Cool set, I walked around looking at it durring the days when no one was there. It looked very real and convincing. In fact, when I first saw it I think I muttered a few words of surprise of seeing a plane wreck.

properties.name: Liliuokalani was Queen here
properties.description: Posted by Tracy_the_astonishingHonolulu, Hawaiifirst and only reigning Hawaiian queen and the last Hawaiian sovereign to govern the islands, which were annexed by the United States in 1898. As head of the Oni pa\'a (Stand Firm) movement, whose motto was "Hawaii for the Hawaiians" Liliuokalani fought bitterly against annexation of the islands by the United States. Annexation nonetheless occurred in July 1898. In that year she published Hawaii\'s Story by Hawaii\'s Queen and composed "Aloha Oe," a song ever afterward beloved in the islands. Thereafter she withdrew from public life, enjoying a government pension and the homage of islanders and visitors alike. Born Sept. 2, 1838, Honolulu, Hawaii, died Nov. 11, 1917, Honolulu.
